   Yesterday was about the past, but today's about the moment everything
   changed... ‚Å† October is national breast cancer awareness month. I don't
   talk about this often because it's a hard story for me to tell. ‚Å† I
   remember sitting in the breast cancer ward as a junior in college and
   feeling wayyy too young to be there. ‚Å† ‚Å† I felt out of place. My world
   was upside down, and everything felt wrong. ‚Å† ‚Å† The tumors were benign,
   but the experience inspired me to look deeper. What was I eating? What
   was in my beauty products? My cleaning products? Plastic??? ‚Å† ‚Å† I had
   so many questions that spurred me into living a more natural lifestyle
   that eventually cured my chronic pain, simplified my life, altered my
   career path, and has introduced me to some of the most amazing and
   caring people in the world.‚Å† ‚Å† 2010 - 2013 were the hardest most
   transformational years of my life. I was completely broke, in and out
   of the hospital for constant monitoring. ‚Å† ‚Å† I was a working
   professional actor out of school when my house burned down, and I lost
   almost everything. ‚Å† ‚Å† Three months after I met my now-husband, he
   asked me to run away with him to California. I thought, what do I have
   to lose? ‚Å† ‚Å† And, that's where I finally pieced it all together. ‚Å† The
   changes I was making for my personal health weren't only better for me,
   they were better for the planet.‚Å† ‚Å† It was so inspiring to read your
   stories yesterday. It was so encouraging knowing that many of you
   didn't grow up in an eco-conscious household. ‚Å† ‚Å† I'm so curious to
   know what inspired you to change? What flipped the switch for you? What
   inspired you to take that first step? To learn more? ‚Å† #goingzerowaste‚Å†
   ‚Å† .‚Å† .‚Å† .‚Å† #zerowaste #ecofriendly #iamwellandgood #organiclife
