   I canceled my trip to New York this September...‚Å† ‚Å† It‚Äôs no secret that
   flying less is a great way to reduce your impact on the environment. I
   don‚Äôt travel very often. ‚Å† ‚Å† Sometimes I feel like the only millennial
   in the world who‚Äôs not interested in that nomad lifestyle.‚Å† ‚Å† I just
   love being at home, anyone else? ‚Å† So, I decided to try a staycation
   instead! I feel like the term staycation can have a negative
   context....‚Å† ‚Å† I think we should reclaim the term and make it sexy! ‚Å† ‚Å†
   Instead of going to NYC, I stayed nearby, packed a bag full of my
   favorite and most versatile @icebreakernz pieces, and explored my own
   city. ‚Å† ‚Å† From finally walking the Golden Gate Bridge, traversing ALL
   of Golden Gate Park and trying to find the best vegan ice-cream in the
   bay. ‚Å† ‚Å† @icebreakernz is the perfect suitcase companion, especially
   for moody SF weather. Their natural fibers are wrinkle-resistant,
   anti-bacterial, anti-microbial and rockstar for temperature regulation
   so you can mix and match their pieces and re-wear them over and over
   again without washing! ‚Å† ‚Å† I wrote a full blog post about my perfect
   3-Day Staycation around the Bay Area, (link in profile) and would LOVE
   to encourage you to switch a far-away vacation to one a little closer
